HEADWORD: Protactic
<hw>Pro*tac"tic</hw> <pr>(pr⟦osl⟧*t⟦acr⟧k"t⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>protaktiko`s</grk> placing or placed before, fr.
<grk>prota`ssein</grk> to place in front; <grk>pro`</grk> before +
<grk>ta`ssein</grk> to arrange.]</ety> <def>Giving a previous narrative
or explanation, as of the plot or personages of a play;
introductory.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

